For this version I have a lot of article to talk about:

- [This article](https://increment.com/teams/the-epistemology-of-software-quality/) on how stress and sleep are way more impactful than technology, processes and paradigms. It's not the first time Hillel shows up in my review, that is because his work on empirical research provide a lot of solid insights
- [This article](https://usefyi.com/remote-work-best-practices/) on best practices for remote work. I've worked remotely for 3 years, for the best and the worst. You should not underestimate the effort to put in clear communication, self-care and time sharing
